(c) as from 15th April 1964 black beer the worts whereof before fermentation were of a specific gravity of 1200 degrees or more shall not be charged with duty under section 1 of the Finance Act 1959 or with the duties in this Resolution, and—


(i) except for the purpose of drawback of the duties charged before that date, the expression "beer" in the customs and excise Acts shall not include such black beer;

(ii) all references in those Acts to black beer shall be omitted; and

(iii) section 2 of the Finance Act 1930 (duty on imported black beer) shall cease to have effect;

