That, as regards bets made at any time by reference to events taking place on or after 3rd August, 1964,—


(a) provision may be made for extending the amount on which the pool betting duty chargeable on any bets is to be computed so as to include amounts additional to the stake money, where any expenses or profits of persons concerned with or benefiting from the promotion of the betting are not provided for out of the stake money;

(b) provision may be made for extending the pool betting duty to certain bets at fixed odds.—[Mr. Maudling.]
